---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Peru Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/peru/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Ecuador for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/ecuador' },
  { title: 'Colombia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/colombia' },
  { title: 'Chile for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/chile' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'peruFit', header: 'Peru Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PEN 1,100-1,550/mo', peruFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PEN 1,300-1,850/mo', peruFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'PEN 1,000-1,400/mo', peruFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'To 84', monthlyFrom: 'PEN 950-1,350/mo', peruFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Peruvian EPS', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'PEN 200-500/mo', peruFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'PEN 1,000-1,550', annual: 'PEN 12,000-18,600' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'PEN 1,400-2,100', annual: 'PEN 16,800-25,200' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'PEN 1,900-2,850', annual: 'PEN 22,800-34,200' },
  { category: 'Peruvian EPS (Private)', monthly: 'PEN 200-500', annual: 'PEN 2,400-6,000' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'PEN 150-400/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Peru 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Peru. Machu Picchu, Lima gastronomy, affordable living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Peru"
  subheadline="Peru offers incredible history, world-renowned cuisine, diverse landscapes from coast to Andes, and affordable living—with good private healthcare in Lima."
  heroImage="/images/countries/peru-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Peru</h2>
  <p>
    Peru offers extraordinary richness—Machu Picchu, Amazon jungle, colonial Cusco, and Lima's world-class food scene. The cost of living is low, the culture is welcoming, and private healthcare in Lima rivals anywhere in Latin America. Many retirees fall in love with Peru's depth and diversity.
  </p>

  <p>
    Lima provides cosmopolitan living, excellent hospitals, and Pacific coast location. Cusco offers historic charm at altitude (altitude concerns for some seniors). Arequipa has colonial beauty with pleasant climate. The coast offers beach communities with good weather year-round.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good private in Lima; limited elsewhere</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Spanish essential outside tourist areas</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> PEN 3,500-6,500/month (~$950-1,750)</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Varies dramatically; Lima is mild year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Cuisine:</strong> World-renowned; Lima is culinary capital</li>
      <li><strong>History:</strong> Inca heritage, colonial architecture</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Peru's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Peru has a two-tier system: public healthcare (EsSalud) is free for workers but overcrowded and underfunded. Private healthcare in Lima is excellent—Clínica Ricardo Palma, Clínica Anglo Americana, and Clínica San Pablo offer modern facilities with English-speaking doctors.
  </p>

  <p>
    Outside Lima, healthcare quality drops significantly. Cusco has adequate private options for tourists but nothing comparable to Lima. For serious care, plan on Lima or evacuation. Many expats base in Lima specifically for healthcare access while traveling to explore the country.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Altitude Considerations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Cusco (3,400m) and Lake Titicaca (3,800m) are at serious altitude. Seniors with heart or respiratory conditions should be cautious. Altitude sickness is real; acclimatization is essential. Lima at sea level has no altitude concerns. Consider health implications when choosing location.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Peru offers welcoming options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Retirement Visa (Visa de Rentista)</h3>
  <p>
    For those with permanent income of $1,000+/month. Valid 1 year, renewable indefinitely. Straightforward process. Can apply for permanent residence after 3 years.
  </p>

  <h3>Investment Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those investing in Peruvian property or business. Investment threshold varies. Provides residence with work rights if desired.
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Extensions</h3>
  <p>
    Many nationalities get 183 days visa-free. Extensions possible. Some retirees use this for extended stays while considering full residence.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Peru:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa application:</strong> Health insurance recommended but not strictly required</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> International insurance essential for quality care</li>
    <li><strong>Age limits:</strong> Peruvian insurers have strict age restrictions</li>
    <li><strong>Lima focus:</strong> Ensure coverage at Lima's best hospitals</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Peru</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for seniors—Peruvian insurers rarely accept those over 65. Ensure coverage at Lima's top private hospitals and evacuation if outside Lima. For routine care, private clinics are affordable enough to pay cash. Keep international for serious issues.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Peru, international coverage is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Peru</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Direct billing at Lima's top hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), excellent Latin America coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Americas pricing</li>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Good US-based option for Americans with US coverage included</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that work well with Peru's private hospitals.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Peru are moderate:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Private care is affordable; high deductible works</li>
    <li><strong>Latin America only:</strong> Excluding US significantly reduces costs</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Private consultations PEN 150-300; cash easy</li>
    <li><strong>Lima base:</strong> Best healthcare access; travel for exploration</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Foodie Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,000/month pension. Passionate about Peruvian cuisine. Moving to Lima.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for comprehensive coverage. Direct billing at Clínica Anglo Americana. US coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~PEN 1,400/month (~$380). Lives excellently in Lima's Miraflores district.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British History Enthusiast, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Pension £1,800/month. Fascinated by Inca history. Wants Cusco base.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with evacuation. Considers altitude carefully (checked with doctor). Lima for serious care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~PEN 1,700/month (~£360). Enjoys historic living with healthcare backup plan.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Canadian Snowbird, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> 6 months Peru, 6 months Canada. CAD $2,500/month pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care worldwide. Covers both countries. Lima in Canadian winter; home in summer.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~PEN 1,200/month (~CAD $410). Single policy simplicity for two-base life.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Peru safe for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally yes in residential areas and tourist zones. Lima's upscale districts (Miraflores, San Isidro, Barranco) are safe. Standard precautions apply. Petty theft occurs; violent crime against tourists is rare. Cusco tourist areas are well-policed. Exercise normal caution.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Spanish?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Strongly recommended. While tourist areas and private hospitals have English, daily life requires Spanish. Learning Spanish significantly improves quality of life and integration. Peru is more monolingual than you might expect outside international hotels.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about altitude in Cusco?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Cusco is at 3,400m (11,150ft)—serious altitude. Symptoms include headache, fatigue, shortness of breath. Takes 2-3 days to acclimatize. Seniors with heart or lung conditions should consult doctors first. Lima at sea level has no altitude concerns. Many retirees choose Lima specifically for this reason.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good is Lima's healthcare really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Lima's top private hospitals are excellent—modern equipment, trained doctors, English available. Clínica Ricardo Palma, Anglo Americana, and San Pablo are JCI-accredited. Quality rivals any Latin American capital. Costs are fraction of US. Outside Lima, quality drops dramatically.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that work well with Peru's private hospitals.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Peruvian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
